@user1:
What happens if the `inc.name` isn't in the `typemap`?

@author:
In case `inc.name` is not in `typemap`, `typemap.get(inc.name)` will return `None` and the if stmt below will be evaluated to false. I will update this code to address the corner case if all `typemap.get(...) = [None, ..., None]`, then, the if statement should be false as well.
